lenders.occupational_info:
What is United Muslim Relief About?
They are registered as a 501 (c)(3) organization of a nonprofit nature. United Muslim Relief (UMR) is among the most rapid growing NGOs in the country of the United States, while their key focus is on the creation of humanitarian coalitions which in turn deal with various developmental needs. 
UMR has the belief that everyone has the full right to reside in a more secure, more equitable world, one that is free of poverty, and whereby they have the capacity to go on and realize their full potential. 
They are inspired by the ethos that pertains to Islam, though, simultaneously, they are not only open-minded but also pluralistic. At UMR, the belief is that everyone, irrespective of their age, their background, or their religion, should have the capacity to freely access sources of healthcare, clean water, to basic social services, and they should equally be able to maintain a sustainable livelihood. 
Matters related to shortage in natural resources, climate change, humanitarian crises of varying nature, famines, energy limitations, and the proliferation of warfare all dictate that it’s more important now than ever before to have collaboration within areas that are related to international development. As such UMR work together with a large diversity of partners so as to tackle these particular challenges in a more effective manner while being able to rely on a more productive approach. 
Besides the strong belief that UMR have in collaboration, they also believe in giving back to the various communities that provide them with support, as well as to their volunteers, without which, UMR would not be what it is today. By way of making an investment in their student-led chapters around the country, UMR strive to ensure the development of the humanitarian leaders of tomorrow. 

UMR’s Vision
UMR’s vision is to become a world leader in developmental services and in the uniting of the relief provided by partner organizations so as to better be able to assist communities that remain underserved in the achievement of helping them to thrive through self-sustenance in a dignified way. 
UMR’s Mission
UMR’s focus is for the integration of their global partners’ services for the provision of developmental aid and comprehensive relief which will then be bestowed upon worldwide communities that are underserved. They achieve their humanitarian mission through the blending of advocacy, disaster response, youth mobilization, and also empowerment through the power of education. 
UMR’s Purpose
At UMR they believe that everyone, regardless of their religion or race, ought to have access to healthcare, clean water, to basic social services, and have the capacity to earn a livelihood in a sustainable way. 
UMR’s Approach
At UMR, they try to obtain their purpose through education of the public, delivering sustainable programs, running campaigns, and delivering humanitarian aid within areas of disaster and conflict.

lenders.occupation: St. Lucie Center For Cosmetic Dentistry
lenders.occupational_info:
The Port St. Lucie Dental Practice

If you are looking for a quality dental care practice, then you’ll certainly find it at the Port St. Lucie Dental Practice. The practice affords an entire range of family and affordable cosmetic services, inclusive of, though not limited to: 

- Teeth whitening
- Veneers
- Crowns
- Cosmetic bonding
- Dentures
- Periodontal health and dental hygiene

The cosmetic dentistry team at the St. Lucie Center make it their sole purpose to ensure their customers enjoy a lifetime of beautifully healthy smiles. From the very first time you get in touch with St. Lucie’s dental office, it becomes obvious that it’s certainly far from a run-of-the-mill practice. 

It has been Dr. R. Anthony Matheny’s sole purpose to create a highly skilled team of associates that are thoroughly dedicated and caring dental practitioners, and completely committed to the health and smiles of their clients.

The patient coordinators at St. Lucie dental practice will hear your concerns and then will work with you directly in order to ascertain your precise dental requirements. Then, the practices’ administrative team will work with you with respect to your dental insurance and also the financing related to your treatment of choice.

Situated in Port St. Lucie, in Florida, the practice is merely a short drive away from Martin at Indian River and the surrounding Okeechobee counties. It goes without saying that you can place your full trust in the skilled dental staff, while they help you and your family to maintain superior dental health. 


Dr. R. Anthony Matheny D.D.S.

Dr. R Anthony Matheny, D.D.S., has been in practice as a dentist for more than 20 years. During his early professionally-focused years, he achieved his degree from West Virginia University School of Dentistry. 

On completion of dental school, he went on to undertake a year-long General Practice Residency in Charleston, West Virginia, at the Charleston Area Medical Center. Afterwards, he would then relocate to Bridgeport, WV, and he remained there working together with another dental practitioner for a further five-year period. In 1996, he relocated to Florida, where he set up his current practice. 

Dr. Matheny has completed various continuing education classes since his practice was set up. By doing so, he can be confident of his capacity to offer all of his patients with the very best quality in the dental profession. 


Dental Services Offered by St. Lucie Dental Practice 

Among the dental services that St. Lucie Dental Practice offer are:

- Bonding and White Filling
- Dental Crowns
- Dental Bridges
- Dental Hygiene and Periodontal Health
- Dentures
- Dental Implants
- Inlays and Onlays
- Extractions
- Porcelain Veneers
- Invisalign
